Concerns about partisanship or sloppiness by the elections referee won’t be limited to its critics in the opposition, though.Anyone who cares about free, fair and peaceful elections in Kenya in 2022 needs to call the commission out. The Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) survived the last three months of 2020 with its back on the wall, as opposition leader Raila Odinga pushed for its disbandment.
Part of Mr Odinga’s grievance was the commission’s proposed budget for the planned constitutional referendum later this year, which he believed was deliberately inflated to make the plebiscite look too expensive for the country to hold.



