The ODM party leader, who is a co-architect of the constitutional changes alongside President Uhuru Kenyatta, was particularly unsettled by the fact that the Sh14 billion the IEBC had quoted was being used by the opponents of the referendum to try to scupper it.
The electoral agency appeared to buy itself some breathing space when it last month scaled down its budget for the verification of endorsement signatures for the referendum Bill from Sh241 million to Sh93 million



