Then, it did the unthinkable last Thursday. A tweet on its official Twitter handle on the day it launched the signature verification labelled the Building Bridges Initiative (BBI), the reforms process that culminated in the proposed referendum, the ‘Burning Bridges Initiative’.
The tweet was deleted moments later, and the IEBC sought to explain it away as a typographical error.
Unfortunate tweet
But given the tweet’s echoing a familiar line of attack against BBI by the ruling Jubilee Party faction allied to Deputy President William Ruto, it is unlikely that the people who have been baying for the IEBC’s blood saw it as anything other than partisan.
With that unfortunate tweet, the Wafula Chebukati-led commission effectively sent out a ‘come and have me disbanded’ message to its haters in the opposition.



